                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">The Why: Problem & The Solution</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Creating demos often means exposing sensitive data (emails, revenue numbers, customer IDs). Users either avoid making demos, waste time manually editing/blur later, or risk leaking private information.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        While there is an "Add blur" feature on the editing dashboard of Guideflow, a more effective way would be to hide it while recording.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                        I propose adding <strong>Secure Blur</strong> feature on the Guideflow's chrome extension that makes it effortless to hide sensitive information while recording.
                    </p>
